pageContext.claim: “I mean, we got approval from Ukraine and I released it. I don't want to do it. Many people heard the conversation that were on the line -- but I don't want to do this -- but we got approval from Ukraine.”
pageContext.analysis: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky has said he thought only Trump's remarks would be released and added, "I personally think that sometimes such calls between presidents of independent countries should not be published."
